At Least 50 Killed In Bombing During Mosque's Morning Prayers In Nigeria

November 21, 20177:21 AM ET

Colin Dwyer

Worshippers had filtered into a mosque in northeastern Nigeria on Tuesday, mingling as morning prayers were just getting underway, when a suicide bomber detonated his explosives in midst of crowd. The blast in town of Mubi was devastating, killing at least 50 people and leaving many others injured, according to local police.

"The roof was blown off," one witness, who lives nearby house of worship, told news service Agence France-Presse. "People near mosque said prayer was midway when bomber, who was obviously in congregation, detonated his explosives."

