Boko Haram's jihadi fighters have been blamed for deaths of roughly 20,000 people and displacement of more than 2.6 million others in less than a decade. Just last week, group was blamed for killing 14 people in Borno state capital, Maiduguri, in what The Associated Press called "one of largest such attacks in city in years."

"We all know trend," police spokesman Othman Abubakar told AFP. "We don't suspect anyone specifically but we know those behind such kind of attacks."